==== 间歇性封锁国际出口 ====
从2011年5月6日起，中国大陆境内很多互联网公司以及高校、学院、科研单位的对外网络连接都出现问题，包括[[中国科学院|中国科学院]]。有分析指断网可能是因为防火长城已经具有了探测和分析大量加密流量并对用户IP地址执行封锁的能力，而各大机构的出口被封也在其中。具体表现为：当用户使用了破网（[[突破網絡審查|翻墙]]）软件后，其所在的公共网络IP地址会被临时封锁，所有的国际网站都无法访问，包括[[MSN|MSN]]、[[iTunes_Store|iTunes Store]]等，而访问国内网站却正常，但如果使用境外的DNS解析域名则将会由于DNS服务器被封锁导致无法解析任何域名，国内网站也会无法打开<ref>{{Cite web |title=中国网警“修理”翻墙网民中科院也被牵连 |url=http://www.chinese.rfi.fr/%E4%B8%AD%E5%9B%BD/20110517-%E4%B8%AD%E5%9B%BD%E7%BD%91%E8%AD%A6%E2%80%9C%E4%BF%AE%E7%90%86%E2%80%9D%E7%BF%BB%E5%A2%99%E7%BD%91%E6%B0%91%E4%B8%AD%E7%A7%91%E9%99%A2%E4%B9%9F%E8%A2%AB%E7%89%B5%E8%BF%9E |accessdate=2011-05-18 |date=2011-05-18 |publisher=[[法國國際廣播電台|法國國際廣播電台]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110521030529/http://www.chinese.rfi.fr/%E4%B8%AD%E5%9B%BD/20110517-%E4%B8%AD%E5%9B%BD%E7%BD%91%E8%AD%A6%E2%80%9C%E4%BF%AE%E7%90%86%E2%80%9D%E7%BF%BB%E5%A2%99%E7%BD%91%E6%B0%91%E4%B8%AD%E7%A7%91%E9%99%A2%E4%B9%9F%E8%A2%AB%E7%89%B5%E8%BF%9E |archive-date=2011-05-21 }}</ref>。也有分析指，此举是中国当局在测试逐步切断大部分人访问国际网站的措施，以试探用户反应并最终达到推行网络「白名单」制，也就是凡没有在名单上的企业或团体其网络域名将不能解析，一般用户也无法访问<ref>{{Cite web |title=中国网络国际访问频故障　温水煮蛙测试断外网反应？ |url=http://www.rfa.org/mandarin/yataibaodao/wang-05122011111956.html |accessdate=2011-05-18 |date=2011-05-12 |publisher=[[自由亞洲電台|自由亞洲電台]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110514183645/http://www.rfa.org/mandarin/yataibaodao/wang-05122011111956.html |archive-date=2011-05-14 }}</ref>。而[[中國共產黨|中共]]党机关报《[[人民日报|人民日报]]》旗下的《[[环球时报|环球时报]]》英文版则引述方滨兴指，一些[[互聯網服務供應商|ISP]]必须为自己的用户支付国际流量费用，因此这些公司「有动机」去阻碍用户访问国外网站。一位不愿留名的工信部官员说，用户碰到这些情况应先检查自己和网站的技术问题。<ref>{{Cite web |title=Theories abound for overseas web access troubles |url=http://china.globaltimes.cn/society/2011-05/656234.html |accessdate=2011-05-19 |date=2011-05-18 |quote=Fang Binxing, president of Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, attributed the interruptions to Internet service providers' economic concerns. <br/>"'''Service providers have to pay the bill of the international Internet flow for their users. So there is incentive for the companies to discourage users to visit foreign websites'''," he said. <br/>…<br/> An anonymous official with the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology declined to explain why foreign websites were frequently inaccessible a telephone interview with the Global Times, and instead urged users to "'''check their own technology problems and with the websites' servers on the first place'''."|publisher=Global Times|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110521053505/http://china.globaltimes.cn/society/2011-05/656234.html |archivedate=2011-05-21 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=方滨兴教授回应国外网站不能拜访事件 |url=http://internet.solidot.org/internet/11/05/18/1423227.shtml |accessdate=2021-08-19 |date=2011-05-18 |publisher=Solidot |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110520225130/http://internet.solidot.org/internet/11/05/18/1423227.shtml |archive-date=2011-05-20 }}</ref>

